curs in the case of \"stiff\"\noverlayer materials and mostly in compressed overlayers. The latter takes place\nin the case of \"soft\" materials like Pb and In, mostly in tensile overlayers.\nTensile films show non-nucleation transformation compared with the\nnucleation-like behavior of compressed films.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Jun 2017 10:02:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-10"}
