related for low-mass planets, in contrast to giants, where closer-in\nplanets are less dense, likely due to inflation. The temporal evolution of the\nstatistical properties reported here will be of interest for the PLATO 2.0\nmission which will observe the temporal dimension.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Jun 2017 10:48:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Dec 2017 22:00:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-14"}
